up here as I'm heading back out.

00:27:03.370 --> 00:27:07.050
And this will compress into
a QuickTime movie that we

00:27:07.050 --> 00:27:11.550
can then send to your mom,
sync to your iPod.

00:27:12.270 --> 00:27:19.380
Send to your Apple TV or to your
iPhone or even make a great website.

00:27:19.380 --> 00:27:22.690
So let's hop down and look at
the movie we've just created.

00:27:24.730 --> 00:27:28.450
Launching in QuickTime,
this is the movie we just created,

00:27:28.660 --> 00:27:33.250
1024 by 768, 30 frames per second,
on-the-fly compression,

00:27:33.250 --> 00:27:35.640
and the gameplay still is tremendous.

00:27:38.090 --> 00:27:41.490
So this is a great example
of how Blizzard has taken,

00:27:41.540 --> 00:27:45.480
again, a synergy of these technologies,
OpenGL, QuickTime,

00:27:45.480 --> 00:27:49.880
the GPU and multi-core CPUs,
combined them together to create a great,

00:27:49.900 --> 00:27:51.360
enhanced user experience.

00:27:51.430 --> 00:27:54.570
Thanks a lot, and back to John.

