So that's a great example of
combining two technologies to

00:28:00.450 --> 00:28:04.110
bring a new functionality or a new
capability to your application.

00:28:04.470 --> 00:28:06.280
And that brings me to Quartz Composer.

00:28:06.390 --> 00:28:09.840
Quartz Composer is a
technology that does just that.

00:28:09.890 --> 00:28:14.140
Quartz Composer integrates many
of the interesting technologies in

00:28:14.140 --> 00:28:19.560
Mac OS X into an easy-to-use framework.

00:28:19.580 --> 00:28:23.960
Quartz Composer is for building stunning
motion graphics and visual effects.

00:28:23.960 --> 00:28:25.580
That's what Quartz Composer is built for.

00:28:25.940 --> 00:28:29.510
But further,
Quartz Composer comes with a tool that

00:28:29.510 --> 00:28:34.540
allows you to build these visual effects,
and we call them compositions,

00:28:34.540 --> 00:28:36.510
in a visual programming model.

00:28:36.510 --> 00:28:39.280
You can launch this tool,
and you can build visual effects

00:28:39.290 --> 00:28:40.950
without writing a single line of code.

00:28:40.960 --> 00:28:44.820
And that's one of the really
powerful parts of Quartz Composer,

00:28:44.820 --> 00:28:47.170
is the tool that allows you to do this.

00:28:47.170 --> 00:28:51.140
It makes it an artistic process,
not a programming process.

00:28:52.820 --> 00:28:56.510
So these compositions are easily
integrated into your application.

00:28:56.620 --> 00:28:59.000
And so new for Leopard,
what we've done is we've

00:28:59.000 --> 00:29:01.500
added the ability for you
to write your own patches.

00:29:01.500 --> 00:29:04.240
Patches are the functional
blocks of a composition,

00:29:04.370 --> 00:29:06.080
the logical functional blocks.

00:29:06.220 --> 00:29:11.570
So you can write your own
patches so you can extend the

00:29:11.570 --> 00:29:11.570
capability of Quartz Composer.

00:29:12.160 --> 00:29:15.590
And what we've also done for Leopard is
we've built a system-wide composition

00:29:15.590 --> 00:29:20.000
repository where compositions can
be shared between applications.

00:29:20.030 --> 00:29:24.640
So, for example, Photo Booth, iChat,
and Automator use the compositions

00:29:24.640 --> 00:29:25.600
in this shared repository.

00:29:25.600 --> 00:29:28.670
You can build a composition,
add it to that repository,

00:29:28.670 --> 00:29:32.840
and automatically extend the
functionality of those applications.

00:29:32.840 --> 00:29:35.450
Those applications will pick those
compositions up and they'll become

00:29:35.520 --> 00:29:36.980
available in those applications.

00:29:36.980 --> 00:29:39.380
So that's a great way to share
compositions between your

00:29:39.440 --> 00:29:41.270
applications or other applications.

00:29:43.780 --> 00:29:47.260
So we've added new and
updated the current patches.

00:29:47.290 --> 00:29:50.130
We've been putting a lot of
work into enhancing those,

00:29:50.130 --> 00:29:53.350
the patches that come
with Quartz Composer.

00:29:53.520 --> 00:29:56.000
And we've completely
rewritten the visual editor.

00:29:56.050 --> 00:30:00.410
We've rewritten it from the ground up,
making it even easier and more

00:30:00.410 --> 00:30:03.280
flexible for you to build compositions.

00:30:04.750 --> 00:30:07.640
So that's Quartz Composer.

