There's a session on
HTML editing later in the week,

00:46:07.460 --> 00:46:11.320
I think Wednesday,
where you'll hear more about this.

00:46:11.650 --> 00:46:15.860
Now, as I said,
Safari 3 now has full rich editing.

00:46:15.860 --> 00:46:18.980
The basics were there in Safari 2,
but now it's really all there.

00:46:19.340 --> 00:46:21.210
So one thing I'd like to
ask you to do is please,

00:46:21.220 --> 00:46:25.690
if you have a site that does
rich editing in other browsers,

00:46:25.820 --> 00:46:28.220
turn it on for the new Safari.

00:46:28.440 --> 00:46:30.460
A lot of times, we go to sites where
there's rich editing,

00:46:30.460 --> 00:46:31.920
but we just get plain
text because they say,

00:46:31.980 --> 00:46:32.700
oh, it's Safari.

00:46:32.700 --> 00:46:34.160
They don't have this stuff.

